                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3697a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in All Countries except
                            Russia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On April 6 Congress declared and President proclaimed that a state of war exists
                    between the United States and the Imperial <pb facs="0417" n="245"
                        xml:id="pg_245"/> German Government. So inform the government to which you
                    are accredited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
